OL,3,CGerry Adams wins libel case against BBC
OL,5,FFormer Sinn Fein leader Gerry Adams
OL,6,Fhas been awarded 100,000 euro
OL,7,F(#84,000) in damages after winning his
OL,8,Flibel action against the BBC at the
OL,9,FHigh Court in Dublin.
OL,11,FThe former Sinn Fein leader alleged a
OL,12,FBBC Spotlight programme, and an
OL,13,Faccompanying online story, defamed him
OL,14,Fby alleging he sanctioned the killing
OL,15,Fof former Sinn Fein official Denis
OL,16,FDonaldson. He denied any involvement.
OL,18,FReacting outside court Mr Adams said
OL,19,Fhis case was about "putting manners on
OL,20,Fthe British Broadcasting Corporation".
