OL,5,FThe BBC had argued that the jury
OL,6,Fshould not find that this was the
OL,7,Fmeaning of the words, instead saying
OL,8,Fthe claim had been put forward as an
OL,9,Fallegation that was immediately
OL,10,Ffollowed by Mr Adams' denial.
OL,12,FHaving agreed with Mr Adams on that
OL,13,Fpoint, they then had to consider
OL,14,Fwhether the broadcaster's actions were
OL,15,Ffair and reasonable as well as whether
OL,16,Fit acted in good faith.
OL,18,FThey determined that the BBC had not
